26 Sec. 5. K.S.A. 75-7c22 is hereby amended to read as follows: 75-
27 7c22. (a) (1) An off-duty law enforcement officer may carry a concealed
28 handgun in any building where an on-duty law enforcement officer would
29 be authorized to carry a concealed handgun regardless of whether the
30 requirements of K.S.A. 75-7c10 or 75-7c20, and amendments thereto, for
31 prohibiting the carrying of a concealed handgun in such building have
32 been satisfied, provided:
33 (1)(A) Such officer is in compliance with the firearms policies of such
34 officer's law enforcement agency; and
35 (2)(B) such officer possesses identification required by such officer's
36 law enforcement agency and presents such identification when requested
37 by another law enforcement officer or by a person of authority for the
38 building where the carrying of concealed handguns is otherwise
39 prohibited.
40 (2) No person of authority for a building shall require, request or
41 record personal information of any off-duty law enforcement officer
42 entering such building in accordance with this section, including, but not
43 limited to, such officer's email address, home phone number or home

