1 address, nor shall such officer be required to wear any item identifying
2 such officer as a law enforcement officer or as being armed.
3 (b) A law enforcement officer from another state or a retired law
4 enforcement officer meeting the requirements of the federal law
5 enforcement officers safety act, 18 U.S.C. §§ 926B and 926C, may carry a
6 concealed handgun in any building where an on-duty law enforcement
7 officer would be authorized to carry a concealed handgun regardless of
8 whether the requirements of K.S.A. 75-7c10 or 75-7c20, and amendments
9 thereto, for prohibiting the carrying of a concealed handgun in such
10 building have been satisfied, provided, such officer possesses
11 identification required by the federal law enforcement officers safety act
12 and presents such identification when requested by another law
13 enforcement officer or by a person of authority for the building where the
14 carrying of concealed handguns is otherwise prohibited.
15 (c) Any law enforcement officer or retired law enforcement officer
16 who is issued a license to carry a concealed handgun under the personal
17 and family protection act shall be subject to the provisions of that act,
18 except that for any such law enforcement officer or retired law
19 enforcement officer who satisfies the requirements of either subsection (a)
20 or (b) the provisions of this section shall control with respect to where a
21 concealed handgun may be carried.
22 (d) The provisions of this section shall not apply to any building
23 where the possession of firearms is prohibited or restricted by an order of
24 the chief judge of a judicial district, or by federal law or regulation.
25 (e) The provisions of this section shall not apply to any law
26 enforcement officer or retired law enforcement officer who has been
27 denied a license to carry a concealed handgun pursuant to K.S.A. 75-7c04,
28 and amendments thereto, or whose license to carry a concealed handgun
29 has been suspended or revoked in accordance with the provisions of the
30 personal and family protection act.
31 (f) As used in this section:
32 (1) "Law enforcement officer" means:
33 (A) Any person employed by a law enforcement agency, who is in
34 good standing and is certified under the Kansas law enforcement training
35 act;
36 (B) a law enforcement officer who has obtained a similar designation
37 in a jurisdiction outside the state of Kansas but within the United States; or
38 (C) a federal law enforcement officer who as part of such officer's
39 duties is permitted to make arrests and to be armed.
40 (2) "Person of authority" means any person who is tasked with
41 screening persons entering the building, or who otherwise has the authority
42 to determine whether a person may enter or remain in the building.
43 (g) This section shall be a part of and supplemental to the personal

